  "texts": [
    "We observe that the extent of this phase remains essentially unchanged for q = 10 and 12, suggesting that it coincides with that of the XY model.",
    "Moreover, for q = 8, both the location and the width of this phase are closer to the XY limit (i.e., to those for q = 10 or 12) than in the case of q = 6.",
    "In the plot, the width of the Z 2 NM phase for q = 6 is ∆(T /J 1) ≈ 0.0065, while for q = 10 or 12 it is ∆(T /J 1) ≈ 0.009.",
    "1, except that it corresponds to J 2 /J 1 = 0.6 and includes CMC results for two system sizes (L = 64, 128).",
    "As the system size increases, the accuracy of the CMC results improves, and in the Z - q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phase, cos(qΘ) increasingly converges toward expected -1."
